bayou.html

Class HtmlNewLine

  • java.lang.Object
    • bayou.html.HtmlNewLine
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HtmlPiece

    public final class HtmlNewLine
extends Object
implements HtmlPiece
    A new line ("\n") in html.

    See the render(indent, out) method in this class for how it's actually rendered.

    The rendering algorithm will not automatically introduce spaces between two inline elements. You can manually insert an HtmlNewLine between two inline elements for formatting purpose (if it's ok to insert spaces between them).

    See also HtmlBuilder._newline().

    • Method Detail

      • render

        public void render(int indent,
                   Consumer<CharSequence> out)
        Render a new line to `out`.

        More accurately, render an indentation string HtmlPiece.indent(indent) to `out`.

        Note that if `indent<0`, nothing will be rendered. If necessary, use HtmlRaw("\n") instead.
